subl filename or foldername in the terminal
-------set up----------
ctrl + ` open console
com + , open user settings
com + + increase font com + - decrease font
com + k + b toggle the sidebar
com + shift + p open menu/install package/toggle tabs, status bar
-------nav----------------
com + p browse/search any file from the system - last opened are the first ones (swith back)
ctrl + com + p switch between projects
com + r go to symbol (@function or class@function) add a @ than com p
shift + com + r the same but in project
----------------------------
com + w close the current tab
	com + shift + t bring back the last tab closed
	com + 1-9 keys switch between tabs or com + opt + left or right or ctrl + tab between tabs used recently
com + down or up to go down or up the page
	com [ or ] indent left or right like tab
	ctrl + m jump between curly brackets

-------install advance new file-------Preferences/PackageSettings/PackageName/KeyBindings Default
com + alt + n create a new file, can type full path with completion
	: create in the same working directory
shift + com + p type and choose delete and type name of the file
	choose rename and filename (new/delete/rename/copy)
	use : to rename in the same directory
---------------------------------------
opt + com + 2 split in 2 windows 3,4
opt + down close
-----------------------------------
com + d multiple select - tap few time and auto select
com + u deselected one by one
ctrl + com + g select all
	opt + left + [ (put " on the left and) shift + opt + [ (" on the right)(] for ')
	opt + [ double opt + ] single quotes // shift + opt + [ or ] or shift '' ""
----------------------------
com + / toggle the html comments

------install getters ans setters-------------
shift + com + p type getters .... in class generate ....

----install PHP COMPANION-----------------
add in key binding {"keys": ["f6"], "command": "expand_fqcn"}
-use {name} fn F6 for auto completion or write first namespace\ and fn F6 or extend a class name
add {"keys": ["f5"], "command": "find_use"}
-click on the hint fn F5 and automatically the use namespace will be added on the top of class
add {"keys": ["f7"], "command": "insert_php_constructor_property"}
-after typing class { press fn F7 and auto will be added prop and construct }
modify user settings
	// Sort the list of use statements by their line length
    "use_sort_length": true,
    // Visibility of properties generated by the "insert constructor property"
    // command. "public", "protected" or "private"
    "visibility": "protected"

-----------snipets------------------
met = public method
pmet = protected method
cls = class
_c = class with attributes and constructor
tt = $this->
------laravel 5 artisan installed---------
do the commands directly on sublime instead terminal com + shift + p artisan choose the action

---------simple php unit-- install manually from github-------Fix Mac Path or open subl by terminal---
https://github.com/evgeny-golubev/SimplePHPUnit-for-Sublime-Text
open subline by terminal to use phpunit run
, + p do the full phpunit test
, + f test a single file (the current one)
-----------------------install php-cs-fixer--------
install globally
composer global require friendsofphp/php-cs-fixer
php-cs-fixer fix filename.php --level="psr2"
Tools/Build System/Build New System
"shell_cmd": "php-cs-fixer fix $file --level=psr2"
select Tools/Build System PSR2
com + B format the open file
added "show_panel_on_build": false to the sublime user settings
-------------------install sublimelinter + sublimelinter-php--------------
automaticaly detect error syntax
set in phplinter user "show_errors_on_save": true
can't save until you correct the mistakes

echo {} > composer.json //in terminal
